text.section:
The commission may implement this policy by gathering and maintaining, for public inspection, various information concerning natural gas markets. Such information may include, but not by way of limitation:
Lists of producers of undedicated natural gas, together with such descriptions of available quantity, location or price as may be available to the commission;
Lists of persons seeking a supply of natural gas, together with such descriptions as may be available to the commission;
Sources of legal or technical expertise in natural gas procurement or marketing, which may be available to the commission;
Transportation contracts filed with the commission, except to the extent that the parties to such contracts have requested that portions of these contracts be treated as confidential.
